EREx-like galaxy survey, and typical values of\nintensity bias. Marginalizing over a shape of the form k-1PL, where PL is the\nlinear matter power spectrum, removes much of this bias at the cost of ~ 40%\nlarger statistical errors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 29 Oct 2018 18:02:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Oct 2019 04:54:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-16"}
